data.description: Welcome to 410 Crestwood Drive in the Classic City with seasonal blooming beauties all around. What beauties you ask? Fig tree, 2 Loquat trees, raspberries, echinacea, rudbeckia, gardenias, succulents, fragrant ginger lilies, azaleas, irises, lantana, forsythia, daffodils, gladiolas and more.  Great level lot with a fenced in backyard and shed for storage and even a little doggie getaway attached to the shed.   This one level home has an open kitchen and great room.  The carport was recently converted to a 2 car garage and includes an easily accessed storage closet with ample shelving. The master bedroom was enlarged to create an inviting and very spacious owner's suite (26 feet 10 inches x 10 feet 11 inches).  The owner replaced the roof with architectural shingles.  Windows throughout the home allow an abundance of natural light to shine throughout. Upon entering the front door, you are welcomed into a multi-purpose room that could be used as a traditional formal dining room, living room, additional den or home office.  All bedrooms are off the main hall and the additional bedrooms conveniently access the full hall bath.  Kroger, Publix and Aldi are all within 2 miles. Various local restaurants are also within 2 miles.  UGA Veterinary Teaching Hospital is 2 miles away and Piedmont Hospital is 6.4 miles away.  Loop 10 that circles the parameter of our Classic City is also a 6 mile drive away. 3.1 miles from World of Wonder Park on Whit Davis Road.  Crestwood Estates is an established subdivision with larger lots, wider streets and the option to join the Green Acres pool for a fee. The $30 optional HOA does not include pool membership. This 410 Crestwood Drive gem is ready for you to make this house your home.  Call today to schedule your private showing.
